column5: I went up fishing pike for 6 days near timmins, tons of fish caught from hammer handles up to 40+ inchers. I dont have the time for a big spiel so ill just post a couple pics.
That's not a gator,that's a croc lol.Nice going!!!
That's great. I remember your report from last year. Some serious gators there. Well Done !
You've got a great spot there!  Looks like a small pike-only type lake?
Pike whities lakers Only ever seen pike though
pictures speak louder than words, beauty report!
Anytime is a good time when tangling with brutes. Thanks for sharing.

Thanks fellas, it was an awesome trip all blackflies aside. Most fish came on a stop and go retrieve in 1ft to 15ft of water. I caught the only nice fish trolling and that was with a big rapala off a 20 ft ledge. It was a weird year where spots that usually held fish were empty and spots that were barren held BIG fish. As usual the long wait to go back commences...
Great work, some nice looking pike!
Thanks for the report some real nice Pike and good pictures .
